modules.description: This module defines test execution interfaces for asynchronous test cases, supporting both deferred and synchronous test functions. It works with `Async.Deferred.t` return types, `Cmdliner.Term.t` for command-line argument parsing, and structured test lists with speed categorization. It is used to define and run test suites that integrate CLI configuration and enforce test timeouts.

This module runs test cases that return `Async.Deferred.t`, supporting both synchronous and asynchronous execution with timeout handling. It integrates with `Cmdliner.Term.t` for command-line configuration and organizes tests into structured, speed-categorized suites. Use it to define and execute async test workflows for network services or concurrent I/O operations. Submodules extend test interfaces and execution strategies, enabling fine-grained control over test lifecycle and resource management.
